.TH "i915_oa_poll_wait" 9 "i915_oa_poll_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_oa_poll_wait \- call poll_wait() for an OA stream poll()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i915_oa_poll_wait
.BI "(struct i915_perf_stream *stream "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "poll_table *wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "stream" 12
An i915-perf stream opened for OA metrics
.IP "file" 12
An i915 perf stream file
.IP "wait" 12
\fBpoll\fP state table
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For handling userspace polling on an i915 perf stream opened for OA metrics,
this starts a poll_wait with the wait queue that our hrtimer callback wakes
when it sees data ready to read in the circular OA buffer.
